  "prompt": "I told a girl in a relationship that I liked her and she says she never know what's going to happen to her relationship. What does that mean?",
  "response": "When she says she never knows what\u2019s going to happen to her relationship, it could imply a few things. She might be indicating that her current relationship is uncertain or unstable. This could mean that she has doubts about her current partner or their situation, and she might be open to exploring other options in the future, including the possibility of being with you. \n\nHowever, it's also important to consider that she could be trying to communicate that she is not available to pursue something romantic at this time due to her existing relationship. It\u2019s a vague response, so it could be beneficial to communicate further with her to clarify what she truly means and how she feels about you. Respect her current situation and feelings, and give her space if she seems unsure.",
